This paper is primarily focused on the problem of detecting individual discrimination in AI models, which falls under the category of AI and machine learning. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of symbolic execution and local explainability, which are techniques commonly used in cybersecurity (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of dependability, which is relevant to the sub-category of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
